Speaking in Zanzibar today, TSN Managing Editor, Dr Jim Yonazi said the forum is aimed at opening Zanzibar?s economic and business opportunities to the outside world, including marketing investment potentials. ? The next business forum that comes up mid this month in Zanzibar will be the fifth one having organized similar ones in Simiyu, Mwanza, Shinyanga and Tanga regions. We, at TSN, want to provide a platform to the business community and the general public in Zanzibar to tell their story in almost all spheres of life, including uncovering unexplored business opportunities,? Dr Yonazi said. The Managing Editor called upon the business community, including companies and parastatal organizations to capitalise on the platform and to provide sponsorship for the event and market their products and services.